tsuki LMO invariant for these manifolds.\nThey also imply that the degree one part of Z is the Casson-Walker invariant.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 27 Jan 2020 17:50:14 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 27 Oct 2021 13:20:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-10-28"}
