{"id":"2003.03245","submitter":"Tarek Sayed Ahmed","authors":"Tarek Sayed Ahmed","title":"Completely representable neat reducts","comments":"arXiv admin note: substantial text overlap with arXiv:1504.05947,\n  arXiv:1912.12114, arXiv:1912.12182, arXiv:1408.3282","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.LO","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  For an ordinal $\\alpha$, $\\sf PEA_{\\alpha}$ denotes the class of polyadic\nequality algebras of dimension $\\alpha$. We show that for several classes of\nalgebras that are reducts of $\\PEA_{\\omega}$ whose signature contains all\nsubstitutions and finite cylindrifiers, if $\\B$ is in such a class, and $\\B$ is\natomic, then for all $n<\\omega$, $\\Nr_n\\B$ is completely representable as a\n$\\PEA_n$. Conversely, we show that for any $2<n<\\omega$, and any variety $\\sf\nV$, between diagonal free cylindric algebras and quasipolyadic equality\nalgebras of dimension $n$, the class of completely representable algebras in\n$\\sf V$ is not elementary.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 28 Jan 2020 08:41:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-09"}
